A man caught in the street with £160,000 of cocaine hidden in a cornflakes box has been jailed for four years. Coke dealer who hid drugs in Cornflakes box gets 4 years A man caught in the street with £160,000 of cocaine hidden in a cornflakes box has been jailed for four years.Cops stopped Guiseppe Trimani, 58, in Tinto Road, Glasgow, and found the drug stash.The High Court in Edinburgh heard &pound;2550 in cash was found on him.Lord Boyd told Trimani: &quot;It is a highly addictive drug and can have serious consequences for an individual's health as well as having anti-social effects on the community as a whole.&quot; 